translated: Örn, Carl Elis Wilhelm, regimental doctor, chief doctor, Eksjö, b. 4/10/94 in Karlstad, son of regimental doctor Elis Ö. and Thérèse Uggla. Married 28 m. Carin Nordstedt. Children: Torsten b. 33'. — Studied in Karlstad 12, medical candidate in Uppsala 16, medical licentiate in Stockholm 22. Regimental assistant and acting assistant at Seraf:las medical clinic 17 and 20, assistant at Saltsjöbadens bathing facility 20-21, second and acting first assistant at Karlstad hospital medical department 22-24, first assistant there in 24, assistant at medical and pediatric outpatient clinic in Uppsala, doctor at Uppsala tuberculosis dispensary and assistant at medical clinic there 25-26, acting hospital doctor at Garn: hospital in Eksjö civilian department for internal patients 26-29, hospital doctor there in 29 and chief doctor since 39, school doctor at Eksjö high school 32, former doctor at Stockholm epidemic hospital 30 and at Kronprinsessan Lovisa's nursing home 34. Naval doctor at Fik 25-29, at Jönköping-Kalmar regiment 29-39, regimental doctor in 39. Written works: papers in medical subjects. RVO (Royal Order of Vasa).
